#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 2. Nālandavagga → nālandāvaggo (bj) | nāḷandavaggo (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn47.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga "
msgstr "2. At Nālandā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Mahāpurisasutta "
msgstr "11. A Great Man "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.11:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.11:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.11:1.3"
msgid "“‘mahāpuriso, mahāpuriso’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of ‘a great man’. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:1.4"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, mahāpuriso hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is a great man defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.11:1.5"
msgid "“Vimuttacittattā khvāhaṃ, sāriputta, ‘mahāpuriso’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "“Sāriputta, someone whose mind is free is a great man, I say. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:1.6"
msgid "Avimuttacittattā ‘no mahāpuriso’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "If their mind is not free, I say they’re not a great man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.11:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, sāriputta, vimuttacitto hoti? "
msgstr "And how does someone have a free mind? "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.2"
msgid "Idha, sāriputta, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.3"
msgid "Tassa kāye kāyānupassino viharato cittaṃ virajjati, vimuccati anupādāya āsavehi. "
msgstr "As they meditate observing an aspect of the body, their mind becomes dispassionate, and is freed from the defilements by not grasping. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.4"
msgid "Vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.5"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.6"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.7"
msgid "Tassa dhammesu dhammānupassino viharato cittaṃ virajjati, vimuccati anupādāya āsavehi. "
msgstr "As they meditate observing an aspect of principles, their mind becomes dispassionate, and is freed from the defilements by not grasping. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, sāriputta, vimuttacitto hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how someone has a free mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.11:2.9"
msgid "Vimuttacittattā khvāhaṃ, sāriputta, ‘mahāpuriso’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Someone whose mind is free is a great man, I say. "

msgctxt "sn47.11:2.10"
msgid "Avimuttacittattā ‘no mahāpuriso’ti vadāmī”ti. "
msgstr "If their mind is not free, I say they’re not a great man.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.11:2.11"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

